The paper deals with information theory and communication systems, specifically the intersymbol interference (ISI) channel model. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of estimation-theoretic bounds, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of Gaussian noise and fixed i.i.d. inputs suggests the possibility of the paper being related to signal processing, which falls under cs.SI (Signal Processing). The paper also mentions the use of MMSE-DFE receiver, which is a type of machine learning algorithm, and thus could be related to cs.MM (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves the use of bounds and approximations, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
